        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> <BR>I've been thinking for a long time... about how necromancers could be balanced for raiding situations. KEI imo is way too powerful, giving players that most likely already have FT (Necros usually don't get FT items) 14 more mana per tick, which makes them get as much mana as our level 49 spell "lich" would give us, for no HP loss.</P><P>I propose Verant makes a completly new spell line for necros, a TARGETABLE LICH...</P><P>Ok think for this for a few minutes, think about how much more useful we would be... A good ratio targetable lich (well a lot better than using crappy modrod2), say at level 60 our targatable lich would be 20 mana for 25hp(Also keep in mind this targetable spell would have a high level restriction) that STACKS with KEI and any other mana regen spell from enchanters. Dunno I may just be talking BS and everything, but I had to bring it up =p</P><P>Reply with your thoughts.</P><P><font size=5><font color=red><b><center>Zeto</font id=red></b></center></font id=size5><BR><center>-Tholuxe Paells-</center><BR><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=125378" target="_blank">My Gear</a></center></font></td>

